
[1]negligent

   NEGLIGENT, a.

   1. Careless; heedless; apt or accustomed to omit what ought to be done;
   inattentive to business or necessary concerns. It is applied to a
   particular instance of neglect, or it denotes habitually careless or
   inattentive. 2 Chronicles 29. 2 Peter 1.

   He that thinks he can afford to be negligent, is not far from being
   poor.

   2. Regardless.

   Be thou negligent of fame.
